node.text:
This is the first episode of our new video series, "The Freedom To Be." It focuses on the Black surf community in the Rockaways, with perspectives on the experience from author and former journalist Diane Cardwell (@diane_cardwell), as well as Lou Harris, the CEO of the NYC chapter of the Black Surfing Association (@black_surfing_rockaway). 
⁠⁠
About "The Freedom To Be": This series is part of #TheBlackExperienceInNYC travel hub on NYCgo.com and highlights NYC's endless and often unexpected opportunities for Black subcultures and affinity groups—acknowledging the five boroughs' vibrant abundance of ideas and expressions. A celebration of the diversity within Black culture in NYC, #TheFreedomToBe also underscores the contributions of these communities and groups to NYC's dynamism.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Visit nycgo.com/theblackexperience for more (link in bio).⁠⁠

ICYMI, the MTA unveiled the first of the new R211-type subway cars earlier this month. 📷: @4cn.shon⁠
⁠
The @MTA will be testing the cars in the coming weeks before eventually rolling out all 535 of them by September 2022. Their new design—wider doorways, improved signal technology, and more—is intended to decrease "dwell time" at stations and make your ride shorter. Link in bio for details via @Gothamist.⁠
⁠
Pictured: A blue-and-silver set of subway cars in an MTA trainyard, with MTA workers in orange-and-yellow vests attending to it. ⁠

Last week, NYC & Company unveiled a new television and video spot to promote New York City and bolster visitation to the five boroughs this summer, fall, and beyond as part of the "It’s Time for New York City" tourism recovery campaign. NYC & Company President and CEO Fred Dixon joined @NYCMayor de Blasio during his press briefing yesterday morning to launch the video and, on Thursday afternoon, U.S. Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer (@SenSchumer) attended NYC & Company’s Business Card Exchange networking event at @MargaritavilleTimesSquare to further celebrate the TV spot and New York City’s ongoing tourism recovery.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
“It’s Time for New York City” would not be possible without Senator Schumer and Mayor de Blasio, who provided this historic support through #AmericanRescuePlan funds.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Further details on the television spot are available at nycgo.com/press (link in bio). #ItsTimeForNYC
